# Example : 
#       Run the ‘tail -f /var/log/syslog‘ command in background
#
# Note :
#       What is command tail?
#       tail : print the last 10  lines of each [File] to standard output.
#       syntax : tail [OPTION]..[FILE]
#       option -f : output appended data(data added at the end) as the file grows
#       -------------------------------running a command in the BG-------------------
#       include an &(an ampersand) at the end of the command
#       how to check What's running use command : jobs
#       or by using command : bg, it tells us how many jobs are running

tail -f /var/log/syslog &